  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 12 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 6 critical, 13 high, 10 medium, 10 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Chişinău (RMO/LUKK); plus 16 other bases. 10 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, cold‑temperature performance penalties and thunderstorm / convective risk  — most notably around Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Vilnius (VNO/EYVI) and Budapest Liszt Ferenc (BUD/LHBP). Network hotspots: Memmingen Allgau (FMM/EDJA), Bodensee Airport Friedrichshafen (FDH/EDNY), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG), Vilnius (VNO/EYVI) and 7 others. Primary drivers: snow / blowing snow, low cloud base and cold‑temperature performance penalties. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 7 airports changed status, led by EuroAirport Basel–Mulhouse–Freiburg (BSL/LFSB), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI) and 4 others.",
